						<div class="postbody">Say we wanted an enemy to be able to go "off screen" but still be firing at the main character, etc. It seems to me the best way to represent enemy coordinates then would be with 16 bits...8 bit would imply wraparound (which I suppose occurs in some games, such as Kid Icarus), or that the enemies simply disappear offscreen. I notice in SMB, the player can kick a koopa shell off screen a couple of tiles and have it bounce back. I wonder if it is using 16 bit coordinates? (at least for the X coord)</div>

